        "step_93qNXD": {
          "type": "step",
          "settings": {
            "number": "01",
            "title": "It starts with real food",
            "body": "<p>We begin with whole ingredients — never powders, fillers, or by-products. Real cuts of chicken, crisp apples, fresh cucumber, garden herbs, and leafy greens. Single-origin protein and produce we'd happily eat ourselves. If we can't name it, it doesn't make the batch.</p>"
          }
        },
        "step_6YCxat": {
          "type": "step",
          "settings": {
            "number": "02",
            "title": "Prepped by hand",
            "body": "<p>Every cut is trimmed and every piece sliced by hand in our California kitchen. Nothing is ground into an unrecognisable paste or reshaped into something it isn't. What goes in looks like what it is — because it is.</p>"
          }
        },
        "step_dEc4bR": {
          "type": "step",
          "settings": {
            "number": "03",
            "title": "Slow-dried — hours, not minutes",
            "body": "<p>This is where patience does the work. Instead of blasting ingredients with high heat, we dry each batch low and slow — around twelve hours — in temperature-controlled ovens. Gentle drying concentrates real flavour and gives every treat its signature crisp, while keeping it close to the whole food it started as. No frying, no shortcuts, no rush.</p>"
          }
        },
        "step_9LxPU9": {
          "type": "step",
          "settings": {
            "number": "04",
            "title": "Cooled, rested, inspected",
            "body": "<p>Once dried, each batch is cooled, rested, and checked by hand before it moves on — colour, texture, the snap. Small batches mean we actually look at what we make. If a batch isn't right, it doesn't leave the kitchen.</p>"
          }
        },
        "step_CtX7ip": {
          "type": "step",
          "settings": {
            "number": "05",
            "title": "Sealed at peak freshness",
            "body": "<p>We pack promptly to lock in freshness and crunch — simple, honest packaging, with nothing sprayed on after the fact. No artificial preservatives, colours, or flavours. Just the treat, exactly as it came out of the oven.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
